casebody.data:
Mary Kaszmierczak, Defendant in Error, v. Tony Jamrosz, Plaintiff in Error.Gen. No. 19,142.

(Not to be reported in full.)

Error to the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Frederick L. Fake, Jr., Judge, presiding.Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1913.Abstract of the Decision.Attachment, § 265*—when judgment will he reversed. Where the record contains no proof to sustain the issues in attachment, a judgment in favor of plaintiff will he reversed.Reversed.Opinion filed March 10, 1914.Rehearing denied March 24, 1914.

Statement of the Case.

Action in attachment by Mary Kaszmierczak against 'Tony Jamrosz. From a judgment for plaintiff, defendant brings error.

Albert L. Hopkins, for plaintiff in error.Frank Foster, for defendant in error. Mr. Presiding Justice Smith

delivered the opinion of the court.
